id: pm-8xr8
title: "As an agent, I can traverse why an item exists, what it affects, what blocks it, and its evidence chain from one bounded graph query"
description: "Provide one explainable, token-budgeted graph read that answers origin, prerequisites, dependents, impact, and evidence without separate full-tracker scans."
type: Story
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: agent-ux,"area:graph",context-management,relationships,story,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:57:48.869Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T08:29:03.802Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-17T06:12:59.865Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "One request returns bounded ancestors, prerequisites, dependents, provenance, linked evidence, and the reason each node or edge was selected; Callers control direction, kind families, depth, node and edge limits, history window, token budget, fields, and cursor continuation; Default output is compact and counts-first; expanded and JSON or JSONL modes remain composable with grep, jq, and scripts; The response distinguishes complete, truncated, sampled, approximate, stale-index, and permission-redacted results; Public SDK, thin CLI, MCP action, and shell pipelines share one contract and deterministic ordering; Tests cover disconnected items, cycles in associative edges, missing endpoints, deep paths, concurrent mutations, and million-item bounded behavior"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Make relationship context directly usable by coding agents through one predictable SDK and CLI flow
value: Agents spend fewer tokens and tool calls reconstructing lineage and can justify every surfaced relationship
impact: "Reduces missed prerequisites, stale assumptions, duplicated work, and unbounded context dumps"
outcome: "A bounded graph-context response with paths, semantic edge labels, evidence, truncation metadata, and continuation"
why_now: "Current context comes from several list, get, deps, comments, history, and search calls while the dependency graph is under-specified"
parent: pm-96h7
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: fixed
expected_result: "One bounded graph read answers origin, prerequisites, dependents, impact, and evidence with per-node selection reasons, caller-controlled direction/kinds/depth/limits/token budget/cursor, counts-first default output, and explicit completeness - one contract across SDK, CLI, MCP, and shell pipelines"
actual_result: "Delivered exactly that via relationship-context summary/role/via/reasons/completeness, RelationshipGraph.neighborEdges, deps --direction/--kind with fail-fast registry validation, root evidence promotion, and contract/schema/completion parity; history-window control deliberately deferred to the durable event-store scope on pm-ju83"
