  "2026-07-13T21:57:48.869Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: all-status review found context packing and deps visualization items but no single agent story joining bounded lineage,impact,blockers,and evidence traversal; it belongs under pm-96h7."
  "2026-07-14T09:43:37.414Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: build one bounded graph-context SDK response joining lineage, prerequisites, dependents, impact, evidence reasons, cost/truncation metadata, and continuation on the shared graph kernel."
  "2026-07-14T10:19:34.281Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: added buildRelationshipContext for one-call bounded graph context with semantic reasons, root details/evidence, node/edge/depth/token budgets, exact inspected/omitted cost metadata, cancellation, and query-fingerprinted continuation cursors. Fresh installed-package proof returned design/release context around build through the public SDK. Remaining CLI/MCP adapters stay explicitly in this open story."
  "2026-07-14T10:48:29.884Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 1 evidence: bounded context now uses browser-safe TextEncoder byte sizing, charges root evidence exactly once, and explains custom hierarchy using registered endpoint orientation rather than labels. Direct ancestor/descendant and exact evidence token-cost regressions pass."
  "2026-07-14T11:06:17.058Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 2 evidence: direct semantic reasons consume one indexed root incident snapshot, TextEncoder is reused, promoted evidence is emitted once outside root and charged exactly once, and oversized root/evidence baselines fail closed before returning under-budget metadata."
  "2026-07-14T11:19:55.052Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 3 evidence: documented deliberate precedence and hierarchy-direction fallbacks at bounded-context call sites for compatibility with legacy and JSON-parsed definitions; focused SDK tests, lint, duplicate detection, CodeFactor rules, and typecheck pass."
  "2026-07-14T11:44:57.939Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 4 evidence: bounded context skips all remaining max-depth adjacency reads after truncation is established. Regression proof reduces the boundary fixture to two adjacency calls and three inspected edges while preserving exact truncation metadata; full coverage is 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T12:58:59.084Z",codex-root,"Implementation progress: pm deps <id> --format context now returns the public buildRelationshipContext envelope with depth/node/edge/token bounds and opaque cursor continuation; PmClient/runAction/MCP inherit the same action contract without adapter-local traversal."
  "2026-07-14T13:07:52.933Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: packed-package temp tracker created a prerequisite/dependent pair and installed pm deps pm-proof-build --format context --node-limit 2 --edge-limit 2 --token-budget 300 returned an exact 2-node/1-edge context packet with semantic prerequisite reason and explicit work/token counts. Full suite remains exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T13:17:41.803Z",codex-root,"This implementation tranche completes the native public-SDK, CLI, PmClient/runAction, MCP-contract, cursor, bounds, semantic-reason, and packed-consumer adapter slice. The canonical story remains open for history-window/field/redaction state distinctions and million-item bounded acceptance."
  "2026-07-14T14:02:00.872Z",codex-gpt5,"Review-round evidence for PR #559: fixed Greptile's dangling-context finding. pm deps --format context now materializes unresolved parent, blocked_by, and dependency targets as explicit status=missing nodes with typed edges and a unique missing_count, while canonicalizing case-insensitive live IDs. Tests cover every relationship form and canonical/missing branch; full coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T14:37:40.698Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 review round 2 evidence: legacy no-active-blocker references are now excluded from context graph construction and unique missing-target accounting, while real unresolved parent/blocker/dependency targets remain explicit missing nodes. Tests cover the sentinel plus duplicate target deduplication; exact full coverage remains 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T15:13:07.998Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 review round 3 evidence: one shared decoded-reference normalizer now rejects non-string, empty, and legacy placeholder parent/blocker/dependency inputs before graph construction; valid malformed legacy dependencies receive the same default related kind as governance collection. Behavioral malformed/sentinel/canonical tests pass."
  "2026-07-17T06:12:21.940Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation evidence 2026-07-17: deps --format context is now the one bounded explainable graph read. SDK buildRelationshipContext gained a counts-first summary (root identity/status, root-incident edge counts per semantic family, discovered/returned/omitted node+edge counts, evidence count, continuation marker), per-node role + via + chain reasons (\"<role> via <node> (depth N)\") derived from the actual discovering edge via the new public RelationshipGraph.neighborEdges primitive, and meta.completeness (complete|truncated produced; sampled/approximate/stale_index/redacted reserved). Deps layer promotes root linked files/tests/docs/annotation counts into bounded evidence pointers and exposes --direction plus repeatable/CSV --kind (registry-validated fail-fast, pm-gknu-safe) across CLI, MCP contracts, tool schemas, and bash/zsh/fish completions (zsh/fish deps blocks were stale: missing context format entirely; DEPS_FLAG_CONTRACTS was missing all four context flags - both drifts fixed). Verification: full coverage exact 100/100/100/100 (296 files, 5767+ tests), lint/static/boundary/token gates green, packed-tarball E2E in temp dir exercised summary/roles/evidence/direction/kind/cursor/error paths, SDK-only consumer proved custom owns/ships_before kinds classify ancestor/dependent through the same packet."
  "2026-07-17T07:12:57.147Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #577 review-loop evidence: accepted Greptile's current-head P1 that kind-filtered context packets leaked unrelated induced edges. selectContextEdges now applies canonical relationship-kind/inverse matching before returned/omitted edge accounting, with a mixed blocked_by/related regression assertion. Focused 23-test SDK suite and TypeScript checks pass. Gemini's three inline suggestions were rejected with source-boundary evidence, reacted to, replied in-thread, and resolved; CodeRabbit/Sourcery rate-limit notices and DeepSource/Codecov/CodSpeed reports were individually acknowledged."
  "2026-07-17T08:29:03.802Z",maintainer-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: latest hosted review identified two filter-scope leaks. Relationship-context direct-node reasons now derive from the direction/kind-filtered root edge set, and context missing-reference rows now honor canonical plus inverse kind filters. Added mixed-kind, inverse-kind, and both-direction incident-edge regressions. Exact full coverage passes: 296 files, 5769 tests, 37683/37683 statements, 26478/26478 branches, 7678/7678 functions, and 36763/36763 lines."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:19:37.025Z",codex-gpt5,"Remaining canonical scope after this PR: thin CLI, shell, and MCP parity plus million-item latency acceptance; keep story open."
  "2026-07-16T05:51:23.568Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence 2026-07-16 (pass #92 dogfood, v2026.7.16): the shipped bounded graph surface already delivers the story's core promise at depth — pm deps pm-96h7 --format context visited 737 nodes / inspected 1223 edges, honored tokenBudget 1200 (usedTokens 1196), returned 21 nodes / 12 edges with per-node distance + reasons (ancestor/descendant/related/reachable-at-depth-2), exact:true counts, and a resumable nextCursor. Remaining explainability gap on this surface is missing-reference enumeration/classification, now tracked as pm-8kch."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:02:22.070Z",codex-gpt5,"A graph-context packet stays agent-efficient when semantic reasons, evidence pointers, exact cost, omitted counts, and continuation share one bounded envelope instead of requiring separate deps, get, history, and files calls."
  "2026-07-17T06:12:40.315Z",maintainer-agent,"Explaining deep nodes requires the discovering edge, not just distance: switching BFS discovery from adjacency() (ids only) to neighborEdges() (id+edge rows) let every node carry role/via/chain-reason at zero extra traversal cost, because the first sorted edge to an unseen node is already the deterministic discovery witness."
